Police are searching for a suspect who allegedly raped an 18-year-old woman in a toilet at Lenasia South Clinic.Gauteng Police spokesperson Kay Makhubela said no arrestes have yet been made after the woman went to the toilet and was raped inside by an unknown man who then ran away.&#8220;The woman went to the toilet with her sister when she was attacked,&#8221; he said.DA Gauteng Shadow MEC for Health Jack Bloom said that he is horrified by this incident and an investigation should be launced.&#8220;A full investigation is needed into this terrible incident which highlights criminality that has no boundaries whatsoever in perpetrating a heinous deed in a place of healing.&#8220;There have been other rapes in hospitals but usually at night or over a weekend,&#8221; said Bloom.He added that the security cameras should assist in identifying the perpetrator.&#8220;We need to know how a security lapse occurred at this clinic which is guarded by a security company that is paid more than R6 million a year,&#8221; he said.TNA Reporter